      "authors": "Davydychev, Andrei I., Kalmykov, M.Yu.",
      "description": "On-shell one-loop triangle J^(3)(4-2eps;1,1,1) with one massless propagator (m3=0) and two adjacent legs on-shell (p1^2=m2^2, p2^2=m1^2) with k=p3 off-shell. Relevant for muon decay corrections in the Fermi model. Reduced via Feynman parametrization to a (2-2eps)-dimensional two-point integral, then to (4-2eps)-dimensional bubbles (Eqs. 3.8-3.10). All-orders eps-expansion is given in terms of Ls_{j+1}(pi)-Ls_{j+1}(2 tau'_{0i}) (Eq. 3.11), with one IR pole.",
